==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Isomorph
<hw>I"so*morph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Isomorphous</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A substance which is
similar to another in crystalline form and composition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>An animal, plant, or group having
superficial similarity to another, although phylogenetically
different.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isomorphic</ent>⟦br⟧
